list.item:
The Joint Chiefs of Staff feel that as much pressure as is feasible should be placed on the French from a political point of view to obtain a clear-cut commitment to:
a.
Modernize training methods;
b.
Prosecute the proposed plan with redoubled determination and vigor;
c.
Expedite the transfer of responsibility to the Governments of the Associated States and accelerate the rate of training of indigenous forces with emphasis on leadership training;
d.
Intensify efforts to cut enemy supply lines;
e.
Wrest the initiative from the Viet Minh and take more effective steps to insure that recaptured areas are retained under Vietnamese control; and
f.
Utilize more extensively, where appropriate, units larger than battalions.
